I. Introduction
The present report contains the proposed requirements for the support account for peacekeeping operations for the 12-month period from 1 July 2000 to 30 June 2001, which amounts to $51,736,600 gross ($44,189,100 net). The requirements represent an increase of $16,849,500 gross ($9,302,000 net) over the current appropriation of $34,887,100.
Of this increase, $7,547,500 is a first time provision for staff assessment pursuant to paragraph 23 of the report of the Advisory Committee on Administrative and Budgetary Questions of 1 April 1999 (A/53/895/Add.8).
The remainder of the increase is largely attributable to: the full 12-month cost of the 67 additional support account posts approved by the General Assembly in its resolution 54/234 of 23 December 1999; the related common services costs for the 67 posts; 4 new posts for the Department of Peacekeeping Operations (one P-5 and one General Service post for the Rapid Deployment Management Unit; and one P-3 and one General Service post for the Training Unit); and some general temporary assistance resources to meet surge requirements in the Department of Peacekeeping Operations and certain units of the Department of Management.
A vacancy turnover factor of 6.5 per cent for staff in the Professional category and above and 2.5 per cent for General Service and related categories personnel has been applied to all posts.
Details in respect of these requirements are provided in the present report and are summarized below.
