The number of auditors and the length of stay take into account the possibility of expansion in the activities of the mission in the event of a breakthrough in the ongoing United Nations efforts there.
Upon request, the Committee was provided with a detailed breakdown of all travel costs.
The Advisory Committee has stated that organizations seeking the help of UNFICYP should reimburse the Force (A/51/851, para.
40). The Committee notes the information in annex III regarding assistance provided by UNFICYP to various entities in the mission area, and reiterates its recommendation that care should be taken to avoid the establishment of elaborate and costly recovery methods which might not be commensurate with the amounts to be recovered.
